40|$|In this paper, {{we study}} a {{continuous}} time structural asset value model for two correlated firms using a two-dimensional Brownian motion. We consider {{the situation of}} incomplete information, where the information set available to the market participants includes the <b>default</b> <b>time</b> of each firm and the periodic asset value reports. In this situation, the <b>default</b> <b>time</b> of each firm becomes a totally inaccessible stopping time to the market participants. The original structural model is first transformed to a reduced-form model. Then the conditional distribution of the <b>default</b> <b>time</b> together with the asset value of each name are derived. We prove {{the existence of the}} intensity processes of <b>default</b> <b>times</b> and also give the explicit form of the intensity processes. Numerical studies on the intensities of the two correlated names are conducted for some special cases. We also indicate the possible future research extension into three names case by considering a special correlation structure. Comment: 24 pages, 6 figure...|$|R
